 story of the rise and fall of Latin America's new left; and a story of the Anthropocene writ large, about the long-term, paradoxical consequences of destroying ecosystems in the name of human welfare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aSoybean industryzParaguay. 0aSoyfoods industryzParaguay. 0aSustainable agriculturexPolitical aspectszParaguay. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  asoy farming.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478007487zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478007487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478007487/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020